died preconception.', 994, 0), (156888, 'I learn so much that I previously did not know about the world of the immobile that it is hard to believe it all takes place over a few hours. At random: I learn about the casual indifference of the London cabbie to the wheelchair user and that the clearance on accessible entrances is measured in millimetres less than a knuckle. I learn how intractable it is to push a grown man around for hours and how spontaneity is the privilege of the able-bodied. In solid counterpart to all this grief, I learn about the lengths nurses are prepared to go to assist a purely recreational and ambitious project by one of their patients.', 29488, 0), (156889, 'They got to live before they can afford to die.', 1070, 0), (156890, 'Nothing is more tragic than failure to discover one’s true business in life, or to find that one has drifted or been forced by circumstance into an uncongenial calling.', 2575, 0), (156891, 'Earth is for living only', 29489, 0), (156892, 'Nothing is more painful than the loneliness of being with someone who is never completely there.', 923, 0), (156893, 'Life is sacred gift.', 2878, 0), (156894, 'Which soul shall escape the power of the grave?.', 2878, 0), (156895, 'How do you wish to live in lifetime existence; envying, hating and loving? It is better to live life loving', 2878, 0), (156896, 'Achieving your heart’s desires is the key to living a life of bliss.', 11173, 0), (156897, 'I try not to judge people. It''s wrong and unfair and a terrible way to go about being a human.', 29490, 0), (156898, 'Living life is the greatest miracle.', 2878, 0), (156899, 'Live fuller life while you can still breathe.', 2878, 0), (156900, 'There’s no rerun of life. Rejoice while there’s breathe.', 2878, 0);
