and not complicated.', 15715, 0), (157062, 'Living isa thing you donow or never --which do you?', 2937, 0), (157063, 'Thinking of things" is but a special way of dealing with them; but, as is obvious, it is a secondary manner of doing so and thus presupposes another [i.e., the primordial one]. The fundamental error—the "intellectualist" error—committed in Greece and modern Europe is tantamount to presupposing the opposite and to regarding one''s intellectual manner of relating to things as one''s primordial way of living. Descartes thus dared to define a human being, that is, the one living or "self," as une chose qui pense d''autres choses ["a thing that thinks of other things"]. That''s done it! As if living were just being engaged in thinking of things! What about stumbling on them?', 2800, 0), (157064, 'Leaving Humanity is only your decision.', 19320, 0), (157065, 'When your Knowledge is linked together it’s called Experience.', 19320, 0), (157066, 'We live in that grave, in those clothes, in the pressure between nothing and everything, we live by perpetual movement from place to place but we want oh we so much want to escape to say it all to come home at last to the right place our rightful place our rightful space. As if that was possible.', 29508, 0), (157067, 'Living your life without goals and plans is like trying to send a letter to somewhere without adding the correct the address... The letter may get elsewhere in some days', 29509, 0), (157068, 'Although we, as Christians, are living in Sodom, we are not to become citizens of Sodom. . The story of Sodom is God''s reminder to the modern world', 3800, 0), (157069, 'Air, Food, Water, Shelter, Love and Godis what we all need to live.If one more thing is missing, it''s being wise.WISE enough to consume them wisely.', 15715, 0), (157070, 'Air, Food, Water, Shelter, Love and Godis what we all need to live.If one more thing is missing, it''s being wise.WISE enough to consume them well.', 15715, 0), (157071, 'What is happiness? What is a good life? Is it a life without suffering? Something like that doesn''t exist... Life is filled with suffering and sorrow. So it''s no wonder that to those who fear suffering, the world seems like a living hell! And still...those who bravely keep going and try to push through this hell... They''ll find that it''s only a small stretch of the road to happiness. The truly great are those who never lose hope, even when thrown into hell... And as long as we have faith in ourselves, even hell itself can be a paradise!', 26816, 0), (157072, 'I''ve been living for too long abroad and aboard, Methinking the concept of being grounded or floored.', 5065, 0), (157073, 'You know kid…it’s not that every adult stops dreaming because they want to…it’s because…once we grow up, we realize that the world’s like the big bad wolf from the Little Red Riding Hood…it stinks big time and is ever-ready to gobble up any stragglers. It’s this race we sign up for from the moment we are born…if we lose, we get thrown out pretty bad.', 29510, 0), (157074, 'Just being alive feels so arduous that all I want to do is climb under the covers and sleep.', 3218, 0), (157075, 'Doing life without God is not doing life.', 4397, 0), (157076, 'You have no control over how your story begins or ends. But by now, you should know that all things have an ending. Every spark returns to darkness. Every sound returns to silence. Every flower returns to sleep with the earth. The journey of the sun and moon is predictable. But yours, is your ultimateart.', 2678, 0), (157077, 'Exist with me. We''d do so beautifully.', 11896, 0), (157078, 'You will never change, unless you are honest with yourself or you are forced to be authentic by someone that was honest with him or herself.', 290, 0), (157079, 'Never stop loving while living, when you stop loving, you stop living.', 3676, 0), (157080, 'When I hear that people live by the book, I always wonder which one.', 16450, 0), (157081, 'To enjoy each 